article.headline: Pittsburgh 76, Seton Hall 40
article.story:
SOUTH ORANGE, N.J. -- Shavonte Zellous scored 29 points to lead Pittsburgh to a 76-40 victory over Seton Hall on Tuesday night.

It was the second straight blowout victory for the Panthers (13-4, 3-2 Big East), who moved back into the Top 25 for the first time in two weeks on Monday. Pitt defeated South Florida 79-47 on Saturday.

The Panthers used runs of 10-0 and 11-0 to take a 42-17 halftime lead.

Zellous, the nation's No. 2 scorer with a 23.8 average, had 16 points in the first half.

Sophronia Sallard had 12 points for Pitt and Shayla Scott had 10.

Candice Green had nine points for Seton Hall (13-5, 2-4), which fell to 8-107 all-time against ranked teams.
